      "content": "It's not uncommon to have headaches with chronic kidney disease, but it's essential to be cautious with medications. Advil, or ibuprofen, can be tough on your kidneys, especially if your kidney function is already compromised. I recommend checking your kidney function with a blood test first, and if it's within safe limits, you could take a very low dose, perhaps 200 mg, with water. But always consult with your doctor before taking any medication.",
